<h1>Setting up Broadway</h1>
<p>
  With Broadway you can run native GTK+ 3.x Linux applications in OS.js via WebSockets.
</p>
<p>This is not yet ready for production: <a href="https://github.com/andersevenrud/OS.js-v2/issues/29">Github issue</a></p>

<h2>Enable package</h2>
<p>
  Edit <i>src/packages/default/Broadway/package.json</i> and set <b>enabled</b> to <b>true</b>
</p>

<h2>Build</h2>

<p><i>dist</i></p>
<pre>grunt config core packages manifest</pre>

<p><i>dist-dev</i></p>
<pre>grunt config manifest</pre>

<h2>Prepare X server</h2>

<p>
  Run these commands on the server:
</p>
<pre>
cd Broadway/vendor/
npm install
xhost +
./broadway-server.sh
</pre>

<h2>Usage</h2>
<p>
  To use in OS.js just click the notification icon in panel and connect.
</p>
